#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(8, "An ordinary eating out")[
  After everything that happened, Mona found herself at the fastfood restaurant
  near her school.

  School ended, but unlike usual, Mona did not head straight to home. She was
  now sitting with two of her new friends: Nanba Mikoto and Kazugai Uta.

  The near-school area of Misuzu is a heaven for student-priced cuisine. This is
  not unique to Misuzu, as every school in the city was surrounded by a variety
  of restaurants and food stalls. Mona's elementary and middle schools were the
  same too, but this crowdedness was truly unique to one of the biggest high
  schools in the city.

  The fast food restaurant Mona was currently at is right opposite to the school
  gate, so it became the target once the three left school.

  "See you later this afternoon!"

  At lunch, those were the final words from Mikoto after she and Uta rushed to the
  cafeteria.

  // absolute ESCAPE
  // absolute RAMUNE
  _"They said "See you later this afternoon", right? What if they forgot about
    it already..."_

  Those five words lingered in Mona's mind during the afternoon lesson.
  _"What business could they have with plain-old me?"_, she thought.
  Unfortunately, there was no moment for her to confirm with the two, so her
  questions remained until the moment school ended.

  Back when Mona was in middle school, she did get some similar appointments, just
  for the one inviting ended up forgetting the whole thing. Some acquaintances
  told her that she always had that disinterested look on her face, so that
  other people ended up find it awkward to hold on to their invitation.

  Mona glanced back at Uta and Mikoto's seats. She was looking forward to
  hanging out with the two of them, but afraid of the possibility one of them
  would ask her "Did I say that?" if she reminded them of that.

  Mikoto and Uta was packing up their stuff, getting ready to leave school. _"It
    seemed that they forgot, after all..."_ Though, Uta's eyes darted randomly,
  and ended up meeting Mona's gaze. Feeling embarassed, Mona was about to look
  somewhere else to avoid the awkwardness, but she noticed that Uta giving her a
  small beckoning signal.

  Having noticed that, Mona had no choices other than to walk to the two. She
  picked up her bag, and once arrived, the two brought her to this place, a
  fast food restaurant right across from their school for a light "after-school
  meal", whatever that might mean. Mona, the kind of girl who could not refuse
  an invitation from her friends while clearly interested in the whole ordeal,
  joined in without any reluctance.

  _"There was a show that Miyu-tan starred tonight... I'm sorry, Miyutan!"_

  Entering the fastfood restaurant that belonged to a nationwide chain, Mona
  was reminded of an piece of memory from her past self. On that day, the rest
  of her family had some errands to do during dinner, so the girl was planning to
  eat out at the restaurant of this chain near her middle school.

  However, that girl was hesitant to step through the entrance door, and she
  stayed there, standing in front of the shop for about 30 minutes. She took
  glances at the window, but everyone inside was either an adult or someone
  going with friends and family. Some was even close to noticing her gaze, but
  she was able to avoid that awkwardness. Nevertheless, her entering alone would
  be so embarassing, and after that 30 minutes, she decided to just come home
  and eat whatever that's in the fridge.

  This time, she was going with friends, so she felt much confident now. It is
  also worth to note that she had eaten out with friends multiple times, but
  those were all occasions like class gatherings, and she did not talk much with
  anyone there. So at least she was not clueless about like, how drink
  dispensers work or where the toilet stalls are.

  The three got to the counter to order. Mona's favorite set here is the chicken
  and rice combo, which also comes with a handy free drink. Though, since she
  thought having rice for not-a-really "main" meal would be awkward, she decided
  that some chicken nuggets would suffice for the moment.

  Uta ended up ordered the exact chicken and rice combo Mona had in mind, while
  Mikoto took a veggie burger with a diet coke. It was apparent that her friend
  was following some sort of diet, which was reasonable as she liked running.
  Since Mona was the first one to order, when the two asked her what she'd like
  to eat right after arriving, she no longer had the chance to revert her choice.

  The three picked a family-sized table right next to the window to sit at.
  Because three is an odd number, and three girls sitting on one side of the
  table would be weird, two girls would have to share a side.

  Which is actually perfect: Mona, the type of girl who needed personal space
  and was not particularly close to the other two, should sat on one side, while
  the other two happily chatted with on the other side. She expected the two to
  talk with each other until about 6 PM, with her answering some occasional
  questions out of pity.

  Or so was what Mona thought.

  Needless to say, it could not be any further from what really played out.

  The one who was getting a side for her own was Uta, since Mikoto was having an
  unhealthy obsession with her new test subject, I mean, _friend_. Though, to be
  fair, she definitely did try her best not to bother Mona too much.

  Mikoto continued the stream of questions she had for Mona from lunch. Mona was
  attentively listening and answering Mikoto's questions, while actually asking
  some questions herself. That was definitely an improvement. Way to go, Mona!

  Mikoto's burger remained untouched even after 10 minutes since it was served.
  Fortunately for her that it was a veggie one, so it should not taste that much
  worse when cold. Not sure if that logic worked whatsoever, since Mona had not
  ordered something like that before.

  "No way! You followed Miyu-tan too? We have so much in common!"

  "Hehe..." Mona grinned, "I bought her merch too, this keychain for example."

  Mona had never shown anyone the keychain she hid in her pockets, until today.

  "Wow, it's so cute!"

  In the idol world, Miyu-tan was not that popular, so it would be quite rare to
  be able to meet with another fellow fan. However, this was not a mere
  coincidence, of course. Which the girl on the opposite side, seemed to notice.

  _"Most of Mikoto's knowledge of idols come from the reposts that Narumi Sena
    made. And Narumi Sena probably does not have much time to stalk idols, which
    means only one thing..."_

  Yes, it all came from Mona.

  Sena, even before her rise to stardom, had no time to discover new idols. But
  she still regularly reposted idol stuff on her timeline, so there must be
  _someone_ giving her intel regarding this. Uta had a number of suspects for who
  that _someone_ may be, but now that Mona had spilled the beans about her
  obsession with idols, she had gone to the conclusion that Mona was that
  _someone_ she was looking for.

  In the first place, the idols that Mona was talking about were all mentioned
  in Sena's recent reposts.

  Throughout her life, Uta had met a wide variety of people. Despite only having
  a surface connection to her acquaintances, her conversations with others
  revealed a lot of information regarding those around her. She ended up
  classifying people into personality trait groups, which was somewhat based on
  the piles of manga she read. According to this specification, the girl sitting
  opposite to her had to be...

  _"The shy and autistically knowledgable type."_

  Uta rewarded herself a bite of the drumstick, along with some obligatory rice.
  The chilly and sweet sauce melted in her mouth, which gave her immense
  pleasure.

  Even though she acted much calmer to Mikoto, Uta did have much more idol knowledge
  than her friend. They say that the more you know, the less you talk, after
  all. Though it was not really true as Uta was the kind of girl who had a lot
  of friends to talk to.

  _"This girl is the teacher of her sister, which is also the teacher of Mikoto.
    So she should have an extreme amount of knowledge... I want to chat with her,
    too."_

  Uta had watched idols since she was young, and what she knew
  about idols did not come from one source, unlike Mikoto.
  Though, lately, she could barely
  find the time to watch idols as much as she used to.

  Hence, she was very curious about Narumi Mona.

  // VINIIIIIIIIIIIII
  But she found it hard to jump into the conversation. The scene in front of
  her was like that taken straight from a yuri manga, to some extent. Hmm,
  actually it did kind of resemble that from "Our Lovely Umbrella", which was
  going to have an anime adaptation soon.

  Noticing the troubling look on Uta's face, Mikoto said in a slightly louder tone, as
  if trying to attract her friend's attention.

  "Mona! I'm glad that you are here. Y'know, Uta is always so so so busy, she
  would never spend much time talking to me about this stuff."

  "Hey! Did you remember that I had to spend all that time with your silly
  detective game, Mikoto. What do you mean by that?"

  "Detective game?" Mona blurted out, curiously.

  "Right, Mona!" Uta smirked, "Y'know, the girl sitting next to you have been
  stalking you ever since she noticed your name in the class list online, since
  you had the same surname as your sister. She even dragged me in, too! What a
  weirdo right?"

  And thus, Uta conveniently joined in the conversation. She had been eating
  while looking at her smartphone, so she did not notice that Mikoto was paying
  attention to her, realizing how Uta was hesitant to talk to the other two.

  // if so, why did she blurt out that utasama like idols?
  // does uta feel uncomfortable because of that
  // well tbh i can just let it be because she was too excited to think or sth
  // yeah that makes sense
  Mikoto might act reserved in front of strangers, but she was really mindful of
  people she deeply cared about.

  _"Let's see how well-versed this girl really is... This idol is somewhat
    obscure, but she probably can nail this down easily."_

  Now that Uta was in, she decided to give Mona some questions of her own to
  satisfy her curiosity.

  // A-san and B-san cameo lmfao (still temp names)
  "Hey, Mona! You've ever heard of A-san? I've been seeing videos of her
  on my feeds recently." Uta suddenly changed the topic.

  "Uhm... I saw her a couple of times on TV, but she is not really my type..."
  Mona immediately answered, seemingly apologetic.

  It seemed that Mona misunderstood that A-san was someone Uta was
  following, even though Uta explicitly mentioned that she just stumble upon
  her.

  Noticing that, Uta immediately cleared up the confusion.

  "It's not like I like her or anything, y'know, but yesterday I saw her
  collaborating with B-san, so I'm somewhat intrigued. Oh, you know
  her?"

  // this is not canon to pjescape chat sadge
  B-san was somewhat much more obscure than A-san, hence she was picked as
  the second challenge Uta had for Mona. If Mona knew her, Uta would actually be
  impressed.

  Mona nodded, "She used to be from Happy#[#sym.star.stroked]Princesses, right?"

  _"Wow, color me surprised. She actually knew."_

  Unlike A-san who had been maintaining a pretty consistent uploading
  schedule, B-san's appearances were all over the places. However, the
  most dedicated idol fans could easily understand why: A-san had no particular
  talent, so she had to be more active in order to stay relevant, though B-san,
  a hidden gem who was steadily rising in the shadows, were taking too many gigs
  that she could not announce publicly to her fans.

  Hence, anyone who knew B-san must be pretty well-versed.

  "... I went to her show once. It was truly unforgettable, to say the least."

  // pj escape reference btw
  _"What? Going to her show? She meant that live at Kurume?"_

  It was at that moment that Uta realized the sheer difference in "idol
  knowledge" between the two. While Uta had not even once entering an idol live
  venue, it seemed like her friend was someone with a bunch of experience, even
  going to another prefecture to attend such events.

  Uta expected Mona to be the indoor type who barely went outside, but it seemed
  that she, whose knowledge was from either the Internet or TV, was no match for
  a guru who might have been going all across the nation to see her faves.

  "I gave up." Uta muttered, bowing to Mona.

  "Eh?" Mona worriedly replied, "Did I say something weird?"

  "Mona, she was just testing you." Mikoto, who had been listening to the
  conversation without understanding anything, interjected. "And it seemed you
  far surpassed her expectations. Congratulations!"

  Mikoto gave Mona a stick of fries from her bag as a prize for her friend,
  before mockingly glancing back to Uta. Though, it seemed that Mona still had
  not comprehend what Uta was testing in the first place.

  "Is it that obvious?"

  "Yes, it is." Mikoto replied, "A-san and B-san? If those names don't exhibit
  extreme levels of obscurity, then I don't know what does."

  Though, to Mona, it was not that obvious. Especially as A-san and B-san was
  not that _obscure_ to begin with. There were plenty of more talented girls who
  were much more unpopular, anyway.

  "Well, this idol talk is making me tired. Especially because of a certain
  _someone_. So why don't we talk about something else?"

  "I thought you only cared about Mona because of idol stuff." Uta responded
  with her usual sarcasm.

  "No, I did NOT. I said I'm going to be her friend, not her idol discipline!
  Ah, how about club stuff? You two gonna join any clubs?"

  Mikoto waved the fries stick in front of Uta. It seemed that she finished her
  burger a while ago.

  "I'll pass, thanks." Uta immediately replied, "Where did that even come from,
  anyways?"

  "I expected that, but Mona?"

  "Probably the same for me."

  Mikoto let of a breath of disappointment. Why couldn't her friends be more
  enthuastic about such exciting things...

  // 621 mascot
  "You two knew that the most beautiful days of youth are the school days right?"

  "Right."

  "Uhm... Sacchan did say that."

  Such unmotivated responses. And Mona, even though Mikoto quoted Amamiya Sakura,
  the fact that it was an idol reference had no weight here.

  "Well, Uta is a lost cause." Mikoto turned to Mona, "But Mona, you should join
  a club, y'know? It's really fun!"

  "But I... don't have any interests in anything..."

  "There has to be something you like, Mona" Mikoto cut in, "By the looks of
  things, you probably haven't checked out what clubs are available, right?"

  Mona nodded.

  Though, Mikoto's skepticism was only half-true as Mona had checked on all the
  sports clubs in the morning. It was just a way for her to kill time, however,
  as Mona had no interests in things that involves heavy athleticism.

  Mikoto suddenly stood up, as if proposing something.

  "So. What I am thinking is, that we can spend tomorrow's afternoon checking
  out different clubs? What do you two think?"

  Immediately as Mikoto finished her grand speech, Uta interjected,

  "But Mikoto, you were dead set on joining the tracks team, right? Is checking
  out other options kind of pointless?"

  _"The tracks team? Have I checked up on that yet?"_

  After a brief moment, Mona remembered the girl running on the tracks from the
  morning.

  // mikoto wants to check up on club because she can't run professionally btw
  // the plot chat
  "This is for the two of you, not me. Got it?"

  "I will not join any club though."

  "Yeah, yeah, you don't have to say that again."

  Uta and Mikoto bickering with each other looked like an old married couple,
  which made Mona almost laugh out loud.

  _"I wonder if I could become close to them like that."_

  Mona glanced at the window next to her, just to be met with her own reflection.

  Then, it hit her.

  Mona realized that she was not sitting alone. She was no longer the bystander
  who only met her acquaintances by chance.

  God had given her a one-in-a-lifetime chance. But even then, she was still
  unable to speak up her mind.

  Noticing her friend zoning out, Mikoto poked the last stick of fries in her
  bag on Mona's cheek.

  "Mona? Do you think you will be free tomorrow?"

  "Uhm- yes! I don't have any plans in particular."

  "Well, then it's decided." Mikoto suddenly stood up. People were watching her,
  yet she would not bat an eye, "Tomorrow it is, then."

  "That's pretty sudden!" Uta joined along with Mikoto and stood up, "You
  haven't asked if I'm free yet."

  "Don't you always have free time to go play with your friends? So I thought I
  would have to take advantage of when you haven't made any new friends yet in
  high school."

  "Wha-\? That's business y'know?"

  "Business? What business would involve spamming a GIF five times in a row?"

  Mikoto was staring at Uta's phone, which was definitely showing a chat thread
  full of reaction images. Oh! There really were that GIF that was spammed five
  times in a row from Uta.

  Once Mikoto finished her sentence, Uta reached to her phone to turn off the
  screen. With her secrets exposed, Uta had no choices other than to back down.

  "Okay, Mikoto-sama."

  Uta nonchalantly replied after a short sigh, before a staff member came to
  their table, asking them to keep things down. The two sat down in
  embarassment, but regardless, tommorow was going to be a long day for Mona
  and her friends.
]
